
#Check Project
1. Created a JIRA account and Project.
2. Created a API Token from the Security section.
3. Write a python code to list out Projects (Update:- Domain, API, Email-ID)
# https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/api-group-projects/#api-rest-api-3-project-get
4. If required then install requests package ( pip install requests)
5. Now, we are good to run the python code. //


Create a JIRA ticket
1. Create a issue for take a code: https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/api-group-issues/#api-rest-api-3-issue-post

2. Update the code, removing unnecessary filed
3. Get issue ID and update in the code (IssueType: Bug)
https://testingbyme0011.atlassian.net/jira/software/projects/SCRUM/settings/issuetypes/10002

4. Update the code and now we can execute it.

#GitHub JIRA Integration:

GitHub[Webhook]>>>>>EC2[API/Flask_App]>>>>JIRA

1. Install flask modules (pip install flask )
2. Write a flask code
3. Launch EC2 Instance
4. Copy the code on the EC2 instance and installed python, pip, flask
5. Run the code to test the script: Public_IP:5000 > Working
6. Now prepare the code based on JIRA_Create.py code and copy on the EC2 Instance
7. Run the App from the INstancce
8. Create a Webhook on the GithUB TAKE PUBLIC DNS of the EC2
http://ec2-13-233-103-157.ap-south-1.compute.amazonaws.com:5000/createJIRA
Which events would you like to trigger this webhook?
Issue comments
SAVE IT
9. Create a issue from the GIthub repository with commenting /jira
10. JIRA is creating on the JIRA Portal


